# Pre-Push Validation (MANDATORY)

Before EVERY `git push`, you MUST do ALL of these. Do NOT skip any.

## 1. Commit ALL changed files
Run `git status --short`. If ANY `.ts` or `.tsx` files are modified or untracked, they MUST be committed before pushing. Forgetting to commit changes is the #1 cause of "not found" errors on deploy.

## 2. File Corruption Check
```bash
git diff --name-only HEAD -- '*.ts' '*.tsx' | while read f; do printf "--- $f --- "; head -c 80 "$f"; echo; done
```
Every file must start with `import`, `export`, `const`, `//`, `/*`, or whitespace. If you see garbage bytes, fix before pushing.

## 3. White Screen Check
- React Query hooks (`useQuery`, `useMutation`) must only be called inside components that are DESCENDANTS of `QueryClientProvider`.
- No hooks called after an early return.
- No `require()` calls referencing missing assets.
- No new files in tab directories (`app/demo/coach/`, `app/demo/client/`) unless registered in `tabDefs`.

## 4. Build Check
Run `npx tsc --noEmit` and `npx expo export --platform web` — both must exit 0.

A Cursor hook at `.cursor/hooks/pre-push-check.sh` will warn automatically, but you must still fix any issues it flags.
